# Unified Add Item Screen

This plan details the process for refactoring the existing `add_grocery` screen into a unified `add_item` screen that supports both Grocery and Kitchen Tool modes.

## Proposed Changes

### Folder and File Renames
- **[RENAME]** `lib/screens/add_grocery/` -> `lib/screens/add_item/`
- **[RENAME]** `lib/screens/add_item/add_grocery_screen.dart` -> `lib/screens/add_item/add_item_screen.dart`
- **[RENAME]** `lib/screens/add_item/widgets/add_item_form.dart` -> `lib/screens/add_item/widgets/grocery_form.dart`

### lib/screens/add_item/widgets/shared/
Extract shared components from the old form to be reused in both forms:
- **[NEW]** `custom_input.dart`: Reusable text input.
- **[NEW]** `custom_dropdown.dart`: Reusable dropdown.
- **[NEW]** `category_card.dart`: Reusable category card.
- **[NEW]** `photo_upload_card.dart`: Reusable photo upload card.
- **[NEW]** `section_title.dart`: Reusable section title text.

### lib/screens/add_item/widgets/
- **[MODIFY]** `add_item_toggle.dart`: Modify to accept `isGrocery` as a parameter and an `onToggle` callback to pass the selected state to the parent screen.
- **[MODIFY]** `grocery_form.dart`: Update to use the shared widgets from the `shared` folder instead of private classes/methods.
- **[NEW]** `kitchen_tool_form.dart`: Create a new form using shared widgets specifically tailored for Kitchen Tools (e.g. Material Dropdown, Purchase Date).

### lib/screens/add_item/
- **[MODIFY]** `add_item_screen.dart`: Manage the `isGrocery` state. Add an `AnimatedSwitcher` to seamlessly transition between `GroceryForm` and `KitchenToolForm` based on the toggle.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
N/A

### Manual Verification
1. Open the app and navigate to the Add Item Screen.
2. Verify the toggle visually changes between "Grocery" and "Kitchen Tool" modes.
3. Check the transition animation between forms.
4. Ensure the correct fields (e.g. "Kitchen Tool" has Material dropdown) are present.
5. Verify the responsive layout uses `SingleChildScrollView` to prevent overflow.
